snippet.description:
هذا الفيديو معدّ لأغراض ترفيهية. ولا نقدم أيّ ضمانات بشأن سلامة المحتوى، شموليته أو موثوقيته. أيّ إجراء تقوم به بناءً على المعلومات الواردة في هذا الفيديو هو حصراً مسؤوليتك الخاصة، ولن نكون مسؤولين عن أيّ أضرار أو خسائر. مسؤولية تحرّي الحكمة والحيطة وإجراءات السلامة تقع على عاتق المشاهد إن كان يخطط لتقليد ما يراه في الفيديو.
قد يظهر في الفيديو التالي نشاط تم تنفيذه بواسطة ممثلين ضمن بيئة خاضعة للرقابة - يرجى توخي الحذر إن كنت تخطط لتنفيذه بنفسك.

snippet.description:
Donald Trump has ambushed South African President Cyril Ramaphosa during a meeting at the White House by playing videos which he claimed pertained to allegations of genocide in South Africa.

The US president was hosting the South African leader, who sat quietly while the footage was played, and Mr Ramaphosa later said: "I'd like to know where that is because this [the videos] I've never seen".

Videos were shown of South African officials allegedly calling for violence against white farmers.

snippet.description:
Donald Trump is hosting Cyril Ramaphosa, the South African president, at the White House in a bid to reset relations between the two countries after months of tensions.

The meeting comes after Mr Trump accused Pretoria of carrying out a “genocide” against white Afrikaner farmers, allegations South Africa has vehemently denied.

Earlier this month the Trump administration welcomed 59 white South Africans as refugees who have claimed they have been discriminated against because of their race.

Mr Ramaphosa has said those arriving in the US are “cowards” and “do not fit the bill” for refugees.
